    <h2 class="page-header h1">Buttons</h2>

    <div class="buttons-options example">
      <h3>Options</h3>
      <p>You can create a simple button by applying the <code>.btn</code> class to a <code>&lt;button&gt;</code> element. Adding <strong>one</strong> of the five additional classes will give it extra style.</p>
      <button class="btn-default">Default</button>
      <button class="btn-primary">Primary</button>
      <button class="btn-secondary">Secondary</button>
      <button class="btn-tertiary">Tertiary</button>
      <button class="btn-destruct">Destruct</button>
    </div>

    <div class="buttons-disabled example">
      <h3>Disabled</h3>
      <p>Set the <code>disabled</code> attibute to prevent button events from occuring.</p>
      <button class="btn-primary" disabled="disabled">Primary</button>
    </div>

    <div class="buttons-icons example">
      <h3>With Icons</h3>
      <p>Add an <strong>icon</strong> to a button by applying the <code>.btn-icon</code> class and appending a <code>&lt;span&gt;</code> element with an <code>.icon</code> class. This works best using an icon font.</p>
      <button class="btn-primary btn-icon">Primary<span class="icon">&blacktriangledown;</span></button>
      <button class="btn-tertiary btn-icon">Add<span class="icon">+</span></button>
      <button class="btn-destruct btn-icon">Remove<span class="icon">-</span></button>
    </div>

    <div class="buttons-subtext example">
      <h3>With Subtext</h3>
      <p>Add <strong>subtext</strong> to a button by applying the <code>.btn-icon</code> class and appending a <code>&lt;span&gt;</code> element with a <code>.subtext</code> class.</p>
      <button class="btn-secondary btn-icon">Audiences<span class="subtext">(4,567)</span></button>
    </div>

    <div class="buttons-icons-subtext example">
      <h3>With Icons and Subtext</h3>
      <p>Add an icon and subtext to a button by applying the <code>.btn-icon</code> class and appending a <code>&lt;span&gt;</code> element with a <code>.subtext</code> class.</p>
      <button class="btn-primary btn-icon">Users<span class="subtext">(544)</span><span class="icon">&blacktriangledown;</span></button>
    </div>

